When #Bitcoin made new ATHs one year earlier than usual in March 2024, it created the first derailment of any kind that the Halving Cycles Theory has ever seen.

Price showed it could be 1 year accelerated, on track for forming a top late this year.

Could anything set us back on track for a top late 2025 as usual?

There is one possibility...

With the huge positive move following ETFs being out of character, what if it was a fluke move?

To prove this, price would need to extend the time it takes to reach ATHs again by over 7 months, past November 28th which starts our normal Red Year when ATHs are made.

It's a tall order, but possible. 

Otherwise, Bitcoin still remains on track for a top earlier than normal which breaks the so far set in stone 4 year cycles as the Halving Cycles Theory depicts them.

cleaned_data.original_text:
wen Dookey Dash? [long, sorry]

some updates: The competitive part of Dookey Dash is pretty well cooked and many of you have gotten a chance to playtest the game in some form, either at NFT Paris, in Dubai at Token2049, or as part of our gaming council. THANK YOU for being part of testing and dealing with bugs as we QA the shit out of the game.

A not-final build of the game is currently live in the Philippines and Australia for testing. This version is missing a ton of features we‚Äôve been busy building with @farawaygg, as well as many completed parts of the game that we can‚Äôt push live until Season 1 begins.

What are we adding? A bunch of things to make the game more casual-friendly. 

Stuff like:

-NEW MAPS: More to explore than just the same 'ol sewer

-ARCADE MODE: A new objective-based game mode, with clear conditions for progressing (like "dash through five walls to win," etc). Arcade mode is broken up into levels, and achieving goals gets you progress on the map and onto the next stage. Basically, think Candy Crush.

-CHAMPIONSHIP MODE: This is the good old leaderboard-based DDU for hardcore players.

-WEEKLY TOURNAMENTS: Compete in weekly tournaments to win boxes featuring new characters, vehicles, banners, etc. Opening up boxes will grant you Dookey Points, which you can spend to spin for a chance at a Golden Plunger ‚Äì you‚Äôll need a Golden Plunger in order to compete in the $1m esports championship at the end of the season.

-DAILY QUESTS: Rotating set of quests with a range of possible rewards

It‚Äôs a LOT of new upgrades to Dookey Dash, all with the aim of making the game fun for everyone and not just twitchy nerds with fast reflexes. Looking forward to getting my mom to play.

All that said, I don‚Äôt want to push this sucker live until I feel like we‚Äôve got the best game possible. Good news is, all the new features will be out of dev later this month, and we‚Äôll be able to give an update on launch date then. Some very work-in-progress screenshots and vids here. [last tweet]

Fundamental Analysis

‚óè Macroeconomic Data
Today, we have data from,
         ‚óã US unemployment claims,
         ‚óã US flash manufacturing PMI,
         ‚óã US flash services PMI,
to either weaken the dollar index, so #Bitcoin can have a little pump and support at its current price level. 
But, an unfavourable overall outcome may dump it.

‚óè US Spot #Ethereum ETF approval
A positive and favourable news about SEC's decision on #Ethereum ETF approval today and the rest of this week may impact on #Bitcoin and other crypto assets just like what spot #Bitcoin ETF approval and launch did in January.

‚óè Crypto assets Bills and Legislators' talks
Some legislators' have spoken publicly about crypto assets lately and bills being introduced and/or passed in the House concerning organized oversight of crypto assets. News developing around this isn't convincingly positive enough for big investors. So, we wait for a very striking outcome. I personally think non of these would have significant impact until the US election comes.

Technical Analysis

‚óè #Bitcoin now has support at $68.6k, where the wedge top and a key R/S level coincide. Daily close above this price, we will see $71.5k, $72.5k and possibly the new ATH $73.8k taken out.

‚óè Come what may, with this current price action, it will be hard to see it drop below $65k, in case any dump happens soon. I'm still bullish on #Bitcoin

cleaned_data.original_text:
Bitcoin undeniably follows a power law, with an R2 of 97%.

Bitcoin has followed a power law for 9 orders of magnitude. The probability of that happening by chance is so close to zero that it is ridiculous to begin explaining why that could happen to be random. A trained eye will recognize the pattern in a few second if presented with the right evidence (a straight line on a log-log graph over several orders of magnitude).

In fact, Bitcoins relationship with the power law is so strong that it is even hard to compare it with natural occuring phenomena (there are many power laws in nature).

Bitcoin being a real power law also means it's scale invariant. In the case of Bitcoin, Price, Hash rate and Addresses are all power laws of each other and of time.

Bitcoins price is going up with the power of time^6.

So what will the price be in X years, I hear you ask. Well:

"If you double the time Bitcoin has been in existence, so another 15 years we have 2^6=64, so 64x the price now. That would put Bitcoin close to $4M per coin" 
- @Giovann35084111

If you're in the need (you probably are) of a framework or a lens through which you can try to understand Bitcoin, its price movement and volatility, this is it. No bullsh*t, just pure science. 
 
When you are ready and want to learn more about Bitcoins power law, the main account to follow is @Giovann35084111. Other notable and highly recommended accounts include @dotkrueger @bensig @moneyordebt

(Note about the picture: A straight line on a log-log scale is a signature of the presence of the power law)

So far that has been as low as 2 weeks, and up to 15 weeks.

Let's keep up this much healthier gradual climb!

If you have more than a quarter of a #Bitcoin¬†
                                                                                               
Congrats ü•≥
                                  
You will own more Bitcoin than the millionaires who do not have any, 

Let's Calculate,

Right now, 

92% of all the Bitcoins that will ever exist are already in the market. 

There will only ever be 21 million Bitcoins.

In fact, it might be less, possibly closer to 15 million, because at least six million have been lost forever. 

What does 15 million signify? 

For context, 

This means, hypothetically, if every millionaire wanted just half a Bitcoin, they couldn't obtain it due to a supply shortage. 

As of 2024, there are 64 million millionaires. 

Dividing those numbers indicates the most anyone could acquire at that rate is 0.24.
